# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ship-readiness coverage (Phase 15)
#
# Rationale:
#   - CI workflows and Dependabot config can publish binaries, rotate secrets,
#     or expand the supply-chain attack surface. Security must approve.
#   - The auto-updater signs binaries with an Ed25519 key; the embedded
#     PublicKey constant is the trust root. Any change here can let an attacker
#     push a "legitimate" update to every user. Security alone owns this file.
#   - go.mod / go.sum govern the entire dependency graph. A poisoned transitive
#     dependency is one of the most realistic v0.1.0 supply-chain risks; the
#     core team must review every bump.
#   - The remaining paths below are the components that physically touch the
#     user's machine (gatekeeper decisions, audit writes, kill-switch triggers,
#     model output sanitizers, computer-use actuators, secret storage). They
#     inherit the existing safety-bar and require a joint security + core
#     review so neither team can change the contract alone.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CI, release, and supply-chain automation
/.github/workflows/       @synaptic/security @synaptic/core
/.github/dependabot.yml   @synaptic/security

# Auto-updater: Ed25519-signed binary updates. The trust root lives here.
/internal/updater/        @synaptic/security @synaptic/core
/internal/updater/updater.go @synaptic/security

# Dependency graph
/go.mod                    @synaptic/core
/go.sum                    @synaptic/core

# Safety-critical subsystems (already partially covered; tightened to ensure
# every change is reviewed by both core and security).
/internal/secrets/         @synaptic/security @synaptic/core
/internal/gatekeeper/      @synaptic/security @synaptic/core
/internal/audit/           @synaptic/security
/internal/halt/            @synaptic/security @synaptic/core
/internal/sanitize/        @synaptic/security
/internal/computeruse/     @synaptic/security @synaptic/core
